							p'y = sin(theta) * (px-ox) + cos(theta) * (py-oy) + oy

							X^2/a^2+Y^2/b^2
							is less than 1, the point P lies inside the ellipse. If it equals 1, it is right on
							the ellipse. If it is greater than 1, P is outside.

